<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BIXBY-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KC LIFE INSURANCE VICE CHAIRMAN DIES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JENNIFER MANN  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Walter E. Bixby Jr., vice chairman of Kansas City Life Insurance
Co., died early Monday at Research Medical Center after a
three-month battle with lung cancer.
</P>
<P>
   Bixby, 67, had been the insurance company's vice chairman since
April 1998. Bixby was president of Kansas City Life from 1990 to
1998 and was just the sixth president in the company's history,
which spans more than a century.
</P>
<P>
   As president, Bixby followed in the footsteps of his older
brother, J.R. Bixby, and their father, Walter E. Bixby Sr.
</P>
<P>
   He started his career at Kansas City Life in 1945, while in high
school. He earned a degree in business administration at the
University of Missouri-Columbia and served two years in the Air
Force.
</P>
<P>
   Bixby started working full time at the company in 1955. In 1966
he was elected to the board of Kansas City Life and was named a
vice chairman in 1974.
</P>
<P>
   He was involved in several area organizations, including the
Kansas City Art Institute; KCPT, Channel 19; and the J.B. Reynolds
Foundation.
</P>
<P>
   Bixby served 22 years on the board of the Kansas City Art
Institute and was known for having an interest in visual arts and
in helping young people.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was deeply involved and caring about the success of our
students,'' said Kathleen Collins, president of the institute. ``He
was very supportive in terms of financial support that helped us
maintain the excellence we've been known for.''
</P>
<P>
   Bixby is survived by his sons, R. Philip Bixby and Walter E.
Bixby III; his daughter, Ann O'Connor; his brother, Joseph R.
Bixby; and seven grandchildren.
</P>
<P>
   A memorial service is scheduled for 3 p.m. Wednesday at St.
Andrew's Episcopal Church. In lieu of flowers, the family asks that
contributions be made to the Kansas City Art Institute.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-28-99 0121EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
