<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-OSTLER-COLUMN-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EVERYONE'S TOO YOUNG OR TOO OLD
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     By SCOTT OSTLER 
 &HT;     c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &LR;   &LR;  SAN FRANCISCO _ It's not my fault.
<P>
   It's not your fault, either. Nobody is to blame.
</P>
<P>
   Any bad deed or felony can be stricken from your files if you
happen to belong to one of the following groups:
</P>
<P>
   1. Young people (birth to about 50).
</P>
<P>
   2. Old people (50 to about 150).
</P>
<P>
   3. People who watch TV.
</P>
<P>
   Young people, thanks to politicians like George W. Bush and
Henry Hyde, can chalk up all bad stuff to youthful indiscretion.
``Youthful'' meaning you still had some of your original teeth
and/or hair at the time of the crime.
</P>
<P>
   Old people are old, so we forgive their long-ago sins. It was
discovered recently that an English woman leaked nuclear secrets to
the Russians for decades, compromising the security of England and
Planet Earth. But the woman is over 80 now, so even though she's
unrepentant, they're not going to prosecute.
</P>
<P>
   The TV excuse: A poll shows that Californians are fat and out of
shape, and 75 percent of those surveyed said that aggressive TV ads
are their main obstacle to healthy eating.
</P>
<P>
   Junk food takes us out of the kitchen, saving us tons of work
and time, leaving us more time for TV and lying around, and so goes
the circle of life.
</P>
<P>
   But don't blame me. I've aged a great deal over the past few
paragraphs.
</P>
<P>
   EARTH TO GUV: Gray Davis has no e-mail address. And now Citizen
Walt Bilofsky has discovered that Davis doesn't take phone
messages, either.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dial his published phone number,'' Walt says, ``press 2 to
leave your opinion, the system tells you to leave a message, then
it says it's not authorized to take a message!''
</P>
<P>
   I tried it. The robot told me: `'I'm sorry, the party you are
trying to reach cannot receive messages.''
</P>
<P>
   Makes sense. If Guv Davis doesn't want input from state
legislators, why would he want to hear from Walt Freaking Bilofsky?
</P>
<P>
   OUR RYDER CUP golf lads scored a dramatic victory over Europe on
Sunday and celebrated with whooping and champagne pouring.
</P>
<P>
   The vanquished Euros saw this as uncivilized and
unsportsmanlike.
</P>
<P>
   The easy thing to do would be to dismiss their complaints as the
bleating of crybabies, sore losers and whiners.
</P>
<P>
   So let's go with that.
</P>
<P>
   MARK McGWIRE hit 70 homers last year. But did you know that Joe
Bauman hit 72 in '54? With 224 RBIs, in 138 games.
</P>
<P>
   Joe hit 'em for Roswell (N.M). in the Longhorn League. He's one
of the amazing/amusing stories in ``Baseball's Forgotten Heroes,''
by Bay Area writer Tony Salin.
</P>
<P>
   Excerpt from Joe Bauman's story: ``They got a habit out there
(in Roswell), where if you hit a home run they'd stick a damn
dollar bill through that chicken wire. And you'd go around and pick
them up. And that got to be kind of lucrative.
</P>
<P>
   ``The first night there I hit a damn home run ... and went in
the dugout. A guy said, `Joe, go up there and get that money!'... I
didn't know what he was talking about. ... And I looked up there
and that money poked through there looked like Bermuda grass.''
</P>
<P>
   Please, nobody mention this to Barry Bonds.
</P>
<P>
   BIRD MAN of the Tenderloin: For seven years, Frederick Hobson
has fed the neighborhood's wild siskin finches in the backyard
garden of the apartment building where he lives.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have become friends with these birds,'' he says. ``These
adorable singers bring much joy to our building, garden and
neighborhood.''
</P>
<P>
   Now, because of one neighbor's complaint, Hobson has been
ordered to cease the feeding by the Environmental Health Management
Office of the Dept. of Public Health.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's bureaucracy gone mad,'' Hobson says.
</P>
<P>
   In a city where felons go free, bird-feeders feel the heat.
</P>
<P>
   WHICH ARE YOU? ``San Francisco Almanac'' says the following
snakes are found in the city: the rubber boa, racer snake, gopher
snake, garter snake and the common (!) king snake.
</P>
<P>
   IF WILLIE AND Muni are going to clean up the widespread abuse of
worker's comp, they'd better pack a lunch.
</P>
<P>
   Here's one story: A man is injured at his Muni job, is sent to a
clinic in the Embarcadero area.
</P>
<P>
   The doctor tells the man he has a severe hernia and needs
immediate surgery. The man's own doctor later downgrades the injury
to a groin pull.
</P>
<P>
   At the clinic, though, this conversation:
</P>
<P>
   Man: ``How long will I be out of work?''
</P>
<P>
   Doctor: ``Six weeks.''
</P>
<P>
   Man (dismayed): ``Six weeks?''
</P>
<P>
   Doctor: ``OK, eight weeks.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
