<HEADLINE>
WAC COMMISSIONER VISITS NORTH TEXAS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By J. DOUGLAS FOSTER 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENTON, Texas _ Western Athletic Conference commissioner Karl
Benson met with North Texas athletic director Craig Helwig
yesterday and toured the UNT campus, but Helwig said Benson's visit
was merely a ``cordial conversation.''
</P>
<P>
   Benson, whose conference is awaiting a decision concerning SMU
and TCU's potential move to Conference USA, has identified UNT as a
school that the WAC would consider for expansion should SMU and TCU
leave. North Texas is a member of the Big West Conference.
</P>
<P>
   During Benson's visit, he toured the UNT Coliseum and other
athletic facilities and also met with football coach Darrell Dickey
and Chancellor Dr. Alfred Hurley, Helwig said.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a good visit. I wouldn't want to characterize it in any
fashion other than that,'' Helwig said.
</P>
<P>
   Helwig wouldn't say whether he and Benson discussed specifics of
the futures of either UNT or the WAC.
</P>
<P>
   ``We discussed the landscape of college athletics and the
possible future of it,'' Helwig said. ``That landscape includes a
lot of different alternatives and opportunities.''
</P>
<P>
   Helwig and Hurley met with Sun Belt Conference officials in
August to discuss building a football-playing conference. Either
the WAC or the Sun Belt would provide UNT a better regional base
than the Big West, officials believe.
</P>
<P>
   ``In the long term, it would help us to achieve a set of
relationships that would make it possible for us to have more
rivalries with teams that are more familiar to our fans,'' Hurley
said. ``That should be our goal.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
