<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-TEXAS-TECH-WILLIAMS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TECH'S RICKY WILLIAMS HAVING TO WORK THROUGH TOUGH TIMES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE JONES 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LUBBOCK, Texas _ |Texas Tech running back Ricky Williams has
learned the reality of the old saying that life is what happens
while you're making plans. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``You go through hard times sometimes to get where you want to
be,'' Williams said. ``I've been through my hard times. It's over
with.MDBO/,.MDNM/ and I'm just ready to play football.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Tech's star runner has had to deal with the first serious injury
of his career _ a sprained .MDBU/[ .MDNM/ACL.MDBU/]anterior
cruciate ligament in his right knee.MDNM/ suffered in the opening
game with Arizona State _ and the .MDBO/[
.MDNM/recent.MDBO/].MDNM/illness of his mother, who recently spent
four days in a hospital intensive care unit after suffering from
dehydration that stemmed from a prior .MDBO/.MDNM/stomach illness. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Getting hurt was difficult to deal with, but I'm being
patient,'' Williams said. ``There were a lot of expectations for me
this year.MDBO/,.MDNM/ and I still have a lot of expectations for
myself. But my mother is back home.MDBO/,.MDNM/ and that's a big
burden off my shoudlers.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Williams returned to practice .MDBU/[
.MDNM/last.MDBU/].MDNM/Thursday and is hopeful of assuming his
place in the backfield when the Red Raiders (1-2) face No..MDBO/
.MDNM/5 Texas A&AMP;M (3-0) Saturday .MDBU/[ .MDNM/in.MDBU/]at.MDNM/
Jones Stadium. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't really know just yet whether I'll be playing Saturday
or not, but there's a good chance I will be,'' he said. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Williams is wearing a brace on his right knee. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Certain steps do hurt, but I don't have much pain,'' Williams
said. ``I'm really feeling wonderful. I'm ready to get back and
help the team.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Tech coach Spike Dykes said he wants Williams back in the
lineup, but won't risk the junior's future. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Ricky has such pain tolerance that you have to be careful with
him,'' Dykes said. ``I want him back out there, but I do not want
to do anything to jeopardize his future. If there's any doubt, he
won't play.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Fullback Sammy Morris (bruised shoulder) is probable. Right
guard Jason May (knee) and cornerback Oscar Solis (ankle sprain)
are listed .MDBU/as .MDNM/doubtful.MDBU/.[.MDNM/ early in the
week..MDBU/].MDNM/ &QL; 
\Nsubheds:Retooling Baylor &QL; 
[body]Baylor coach Kevin Steele on Monday proclaimed the Bears
(0-4) were in a ``full-blown'' retooling process. But he said that
doesn't mean immediate wholesale philosophical changes in the
offensive and defensive schemes. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``You're always looking for better ways to execute, but you
don't ever change things wholesale,'' he said. ``That's the kiss of
death. Retooling means looking at the way you're going about
recruiting _ who you're recruiting, what needs you're filling. The
way you're handling the team emotionally. The way you're
practicing. Taking care of the little things. The whole mindset has
to be retooled. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``But the one thing you don't ever do is give up and second
guess. A whole lot of coaches have been in this situation. The ones
who have kept focused on the bullseye are the ones who have been
successful.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Bears play North Texas .MDBO/on .MDNM/Saturday. &QL; 
[body]OSU twosome doubtful &QL; 
[body]Oklahoma State linebacker Kenyatta Wright (knee) is doubtful
for Saturday's game at Nebraska.MDBO/,.MDNM/ as is quarterback Tony
Lindsay who is rehabilitating strained knee ligaments. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I'd like to say Tony is ahead of schedule, but I think he's
doubtful to be honest about it,'' coach Bob Simmons said. ``He
practiced a little last week, but whether or not he will play will
be based on his progress this week and what the trainers let him
do.'' &QL; 
