Americans suffer from vitiligo, a condition in which the skin's
pigmentation cells are destroyed and no longer able to produce the
melanin that normally gives the body its color. While destroying
the pigment cells is one approach to dealing with the disease, some
specialists are frustrated by the fact that vitiligo is still an
incurable disease with no known cause or good treatment. By SYLVIA
WOOD.
