<P>
   The St. Regis hotel in New York City has taken top honors for a
US city hotel in the 18th annual Reader Survey conducted by Andrew
Harper's Hideaway Report. Considered the oldest and most reliable
ongoing survey of its kind among sophisticated frequent travelers
(82 percent of the 2,500 respondents are corporate presidents), the
survey also reflects the growing trend toward boutique hotels of 50
rooms or less. For complete results of the Top 20 survey as
reported in the September issue of Hideaway Report, send $10 to
Harper Associates, Box 50, Sun Valley, ID 83353 or check out
www.hideawayreport.com. Tops in the report were: US city hotels _
The St. Regis, New York; Four Seasons, Chicago; Four Seasons, New
York. International city hotels _ The Oriental, Bangkok; The
Regent, Hong Kong; The Peninsula, Hong Kong. US resort hotels _ The
Boulders, Carefree, Ariz.; Auberge du Soleil, Rutherford, Calif.;
The Greenbrier, White Sulphur Springs, W.Va. International resort
hotels _ Hotel San Pietro, Positano, Italy; Villa d'Este, Lake
Como, Italy; Amandari, Bali. Top US resort hideaways _ Post Ranch
Inn, Big Sur, Calif.; The Point, Upper Saraanac, Lake, N.Y.; Twin
Farms, Barnard, Vt. And the top international resort hideaways _
Amandari, Bali; Huka Lodge, Taupo, New Zealand; and Buckland Manor,
Braodway, England.
</P>
<P>
   In New England, the Resort Hideaway winners included The
Mayflower Inn, Washington, Conn., number 11; Blantyre in Lenox, 13;
The Charlotte Inn, Edgartown, 14; The White Barn Inn,
Kennebunkport, Maine, 17, and The Wauwinet, Nantucket, 20. Twin
Farms in Barnard, Vt., was 10th in the US resort listing; and in US
city hotels, the Ritz-Carlton was ninth and The Four Seasons, 14th;
both are in Boston.
</P>
