Warsh.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS (Foxborough, Mass.) -- Terry Glenn is now beyond
just wanting to have big games. He's now into perfection. By Nick
Cafardo. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-RYDER-HOLLEY-COLUMN (Brookline, Mass.) _ Ryder Cup was a
macro event that became a microcosm of american culture. By Michael
Holley.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   GLF-RYDER-RYAN-COLUMN (Brookline, Mass.) _ The twenty-something
guy spoke for multitudes. ``I'm not even a golf fan,'' he said,
``but I couldn't stop watching.'' By Bob Ryan.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-COLUMN (Undated) _ If psychology could work on an equine,
Artax would be a challenging patient. By Ron Indrisano.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Maybe East Carolina should join the Big
East. Then again maybe not. By Mark Blaudschun.
</P>
