women to sue their violent male attackers in federal court passes
constitutional muster. The justices, acting six days before their
term officially begins, also agree to consider the
constitutionality of Colorado law restraining abortion protesters
and of a Washington state decision on grandparents' rights. By
STEVE LASH.
