<HEADER>
A9044 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r s BC-BBN-CANDLESTICK-PARK-     09-28 0946
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-CANDLESTICK-PARK-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DODGERS ARRIVE FOR CANDLESTICK'S LAST RIVALRY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By JOHN SHEA  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ Tommy Lasorda and Ron Cey crossed paths in the
meal room at Dodger Stadium last week, and the ex-manager was eager
to chat with the ex-third baseman.
</P>
<P>
   Lasorda: ``Hey, Penguin, they've invited me to Candlestick Park
for the final series.''
</P>
<P>
   Cey: ``What are you going to do?''
</P>
<P>
   Lasorda: ``They asked me to go on the field. Should I wear the
uniform?''
</P>
<P>
   Cey: ``Got to wear the uniform.''
</P>
<P>
   Lasorda: ``What do you think the fans will do? You know, I'm in
the Hall of Fame now.''
</P>
<P>
   Cey: ``They'll probably do what they've always done.''
</P>
<P>
   Giants fans, get your vocal cords ready. The Los Angeles Dodgers
are coming to Candlestick Park one last time, and fittingly it's
for the final baseball series at the 'Stick that began Tuesday
night.
</P>
<P>
   ``The fans would boo us, but they were great,'' Lasorda said.
</P>
<P>
   ``They'd have 14,000 for Atlanta on a Thursday, and we'd come in
Friday and they'd have 40,000. They wanted to beat us. The rivalry
was there.''
</P>
<P>
   The teams played 340 games at the 'Stick, and the Giants hold a
180-160 edge. It's little consolation, because while the Giants
played in two World Series over 40 seasons, the Dodgers played in
eight.
</P>
<P>
   But nothing will erase that history was in the making at
Candlestick whenever the teams hooked up. Some moments were grand,
such as Brian Johnson's beating the Dodgers with a 12th-inning home
run off Mark Guthrie, Joe Morgan's homering off Terry Forster to
knock the Dodgers out of the playoffs, and Willie Mays' setting a
National League home-run record by going deep against Claude
Osteen.
</P>
<P>
   Some weren't so grand, such as when Juan Marichal smacked Johnny
Roseboro with a bat and Reggie Smith jumped into the stands to
attack a fan.
</P>
<P>
   After Candlestick closes its doors to baseball this week, the
Giants and Dodgers will resume their rivalry in downtown San
Francisco at the new Pacific Bell Park. As for Candlestick, only
the memories will remain.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've hit some pretty meaningful home runs,'' Hall of Famer
Morgan said recently, ``but the one I hit to beat the Dodgers in
1982 was right up there, one of the top two or three in my career.
It meant so much for the Giants and their fans to beat the Dodgers
that day.''
</P>
<P>
   It was the final day of the regular season, one day after the
Dodgers ruined the Giants' playoff hopes with a 15-4 rout. The
Giants figured if not them, then not the Dodgers, either. Morgan's
homer decided a 5-3 victory that handed the National League West to
the Atlanta Braves.
</P>
<P>
   For the Giants in the early years, there was no greater
accomplishment than in 1962, when they overcame a four-game deficit
with seven to play to pull into a 162-game tie, then beat the
Dodgers in a best-of-three playoff to secure a date in the World
Series with the New York Yankees.
</P>
<P>
   Down the stretch, the rivalry peaked in a mid-August series at
Candlestick Park. That's when the Dodgers cried foul, complaining
the 'Stick's grounds crew intentionally watered down the basepaths
to impede their running game.
</P>
<P>
   ``Well, I still have a cold from that day,'' said Maury Wills.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodger stole a then-record 104 bases that year, but it
wouldn't be easy at the 'Stick. When umpire Bill Jackowski noticed
the wet grounds, he ordered the crew to dump sand on the area.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Giants said they'd be happy to,'' Wills said. ``That made
it even worse. Normally, they couldn't throw me out if the catcher
was on the pitcher's mound.''
</P>
<P>
   The Giants won three straight _ the biggest hit was Willie
McCovey's pinch homer off Don Drysdale in the second game _ to cut
the Dodgers' lead from 5 1/2 to 2 1/2. They lost six straight in
September but still overcame the Dodgers for a spot in the World
Series, which they lost in seven games, ending when McCovey's
sizzling liner sadly landed in the glove of second baseman Bobby
Richardson with the potential winning run on base.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
</P>
<ANNOTATION>
   (STORY CAN END HERE. OPTIONAL MATERIAL FOLLOWS.) &QL; 
</ANNOTATION>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The rivalry hit its low point in the 1965 Marichal-Roseboro
incident. Pitchers threw at hitters during a late-August series,
and the Dodgers were frustrated that Sandy Koufax wouldn't
retaliate for Marichal's knock-down pitches.
</P>
<P>
   Roseboro took it upon himself. With Marichal at the plate, the
catcher threw a ball to Koufax that nearly hit Marichal in the
nose.
</P>
<P>
   ``He said, `You better not hit me with that ball,' and I went
after him,'' Roseboro said.
</P>
<P>
   Marichal hit Roseboro with his bat and received a nine-game
suspension, which may have cost the Giants the pennant. They lost
to the Dodgers by two games.
</P>
<P>
   One of the teams' hottest fights came in September 1971 in the
final days of another Giants-Dodgers race. The Giants didn't
appreciate Bill Singer's flooring Mays with a pitch, so Marichal
threw a fastball into Bill Buckner's ribs. The benches emptied as
Buckner charged the mound, and several players were ejected.
</P>
<P>
   The Giants had the last laugh, winning the division by one game
over the Dodgers.
</P>
<P>
   Among all-time opposing players, former Dodger first baseman
Steve Garvey is second to Pete Rose with 153 Candlestick hits.
</P>
<P>
   Cey, a third baseman, hit 24 home runs, topping everyone except
Dale Murphy and Willie Stargell. On the visitors' RBI list, Cey and
Garvey are 1-2.
</P>
<P>
   ``Because of the success I had there, I was one of the favorite
targets,'' Cey said. ``I looked forward to it. To get booed on the
road is a confidence booster.''
</P>
<P>
   Said Garvey, ``I took the boos as a compliment.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-28-99 1629EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
