   INDIAN-MUSEUM (Washington) _ A century after the tribal
devastation of the Indian wars, a place of capital honor was
finally extended to the nation's Native Americans on Tuesday as
work began on the Mall for a museum that Indian leaders vowed would
celebrate their history of indomitability, ``even if it tells a sad
story, even if it's a hard story to look at.'' By Francis X.
Clines.
