<P>
   TECH-ECAMPUS _ From a modest start two years ago, the Electronic
Campus today has more than 20,000 students enrolled in courses
offered by more than 200 colleges in the Southeast, thanks to an
entrepid team here in Atlanta at the Southern Regional Education
Board. The electronic network of courses, which started with only
104 subjects, has now mushroomed into a virtual university, with 65
degree programs. The ECampus, now bolstered by Georgia's Galileo
electronic library as a resource, is evolving as a national model
for higher education in the future. ``Let's be clear,'' said Mark
Misick, SREP president, ``we have doubts the the web will ever
replace
</P>
