<P>
   FBN-KICKERS _ The evidence is in: NFL place-kickers are
struggling this year because they no longer are allowed to inflate
and deface footballs to their personal specifications. In years
past, kickers were allowed to kick on Sundays with the same balls
they used during the week in practice sessions. They inflated balls
to suit weather conditions and scuffed up balls on cement to create
``grip.'' Now they're kicking new balls on gameday, and the
league's old-timers _ including Morten Andersen and Gary Anderson _
are struggling. (Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
