   COKE-STOCK _ ATLANTA _ Watching Coca-Cola's stock. If the
company's shares close below $50, it will be the first time since
December 1996. (Luke, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HUFFY _ Trying for an interview with Don Graber, chairman and
chief executive of Huffy, about the company's blockbuster decision
to stop making bikes in the U.S. and to examine ``strategic
alternatives,'' including possible sale of the company. (Hulsey,
