other details immediately available. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 40.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Story will move in (f) Financial and (s) Sports categories.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-ECAMPUS _ From a modest start two years ago, the Electronic
Campus today has more than 20,000 students enrolled in courses
offered by more than 200 colleges in the Southeast, thanks to an
entrepid team here in Atlanta at the Southern Regional Education
Board. The electronic network of courses, which started with only
104 subjects, has now mushroomed into a virtual university, with 65
degree programs. The ECampus, now bolstered by Georgia's Galileo
electronic library as a resource, is evolving as a national model
for higher education in the future. ``Let's be clear,'' said Mark
Misick, SREP president, ``we have doubts the the web will ever
replace
</P>
<P>
   classrooms in buildings, but it clearly will reform the way
students are taught.'' (Holsendolph, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
18.
</P>
<P>
   CLONING-EXPERT _ Profile of Steven Stice, Eminent Scholar at the
University of Georgia who is a cloning expert. (Holsendolph,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 40. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Has profile box.
</P>
<P>
   WEBMD _ WebMd is scheduled to close its merger deal with
Calif.-based Healtheon. In the months since the deal was announced
Healtheon's stock has soared to all time high at $105 and plunged
to a new low of $35. Meanwhile WebMD has continued to sign partners
buffing out its content offering. We'll update the status of the
deal. (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   COX-SOFTWARE _ ATLANTA _ Cox Communications signs deal with
software developer to provide interactive services through
Scientific-Atlanta set top boxes. The company doesn't know yet
when, where or at what price the services would be rolled out.
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
