 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS AT LARGE-CHAPMAN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Every year at this time, the chalky, cedar-studded
hills around Granbury, Texas, become Civil War battlefields.
Hundreds of re-enactors dressed in their finest blues and grays
break out the muzzleloaders and face off against each other in mock
anger. The battles they re-create are those of Gen. Hiram B.
Granbury, the town's namesake. This year, beginning Saturday
morning, the troops will fall out to re-enact the 1864 battle for
Atlanta, and the Battle of Spring Hill, Tenn. By ART CHAPMAN. Story
has moved in ``a'' general news and ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   L I F E S T Y L E &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A &QL;
