   DAD-KIDSPARTIES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ One dad says that kids' parties do not need to be
highly organized at such establishments as the Discovery Zone and
makes the case for the simple but meaningful backyard bash. By TIM
MADIGAN. Story will move in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   E N T E R T A I N M E N T &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMPUTER GAME-MARIO GOLF &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Nintendo has never wanted it any other way: Mario is
for kids. Starting with the Donkey Kong arcade game in the '80s,
the colorful, clumsy plumber has fumbled his way through more than
two-dozen games, all of which have been geared toward young
players. Even the complicated brain-buster Mario 64 is,
essentially, a kid's game. That's why it's so surprising that Mario
Golf (Nintendo for N64, $50, all ages) is so difficult. This is the
first Mario game that, unlike all the other Mario-theme sports
titles, you can't just pick up and start playing. Well, you can,
but you're gonna have a tough time with it. By MALCOLM MAYHEW.
Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
nn
</P>
