<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-RATINGS29-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    NBC the big winner in season-premiere contest
 &HT;    By Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   NBC won the first week of the 1999 fall season, powered as
always by the return of its Thursday night lineup as well as a
strong showing by the 25th anniversary of ``Saturday Night Live''
Sunday night, which finished No. 3 for the week.
</P>
<P>
   Among new shows debuting with particularly high Nielsen ratings
during the networks' official premiere week, which ended Sunday:
``Once and Again'' on ABC (No. 14 for the week), NBC's ``Stark
Raving Mad'' at No. 9, NBC's ``West Wing'' at No. 13 and CBS's
``Family Law'' at No. 18. NBC's ``Third Watch'' ranked sixth for
the week when it premiered in ``ER's'' regular time slot, then
dropped to 25th when it moved to its regular time, 8 p.m. Sundays.
</P>
<P>
   Compared with last season's premiere week, NBC was the same in
ratings, CBS, Fox and ABC were down, the WB was up slightly, and
UPN was up a stunning 39 percent, due largely to WWF Wrestling.
</P>
<P>
   Among the new shows not performing well so far: Fox's
controversial comedy ``Action,'' which was hammered by NBC's
``Stark Raving Mad'' and dropped to only 5 million viewers.
</P>
<P>
   Other new series showing well included CBS's ``Ladies Man'' (No.
29) and ``Judging Amy'' (No. 30), ABC's ``Snoops'' (No. 33) and
CBS's ``Now and Again'' (No. 39).
</P>
<P>
   Although last week was the official premiere week, a number of
shows have yet to debut, and other series are settling into their
regular slots after special launches.
</P>
<P>
   For the week, NBC was No. 1 with an average of 14.5 million
viewers, followed by CBS with 14.2 million. ABC was third, followed
by Fox, WB and UPN.
</P>
<P>
   The following are the Nielsen Media Research ratings for the
week ending Sept. 26. Figures are in millions of viewers.
</P>
<P>
   1. ``Friends'' NBC 27.7
</P>
<P>
   2. ``Frasier'' NBC 25.2
</P>
<P>
   3. ``Saturday Night Live
</P>
<P>
   25th Anniversary'' NBC 22.1
</P>
<P>
   4. ``NFL Monday Night Football'' ABC 21.5
</P>
<P>
   5. ``Jesse'' NBC 21.2
</P>
<P>
   6. ``Third Watch'' NBC 20.5
</P>
<P>
   7. ``Country Music Awards'' CBS 18.8
</P>
<P>
   8. ``Law &AMP; Order'' NBC 18.63
</P>
<P>
   9. ``Stark Raving Mad'' NBC 18.62
</P>
<P>
   10. ``Everybody Loves Raymond'' CBS 18.3
</P>
<P>
   Phil Kloer writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
