<P>
   NEWYORK-SENATE (Washington) _ New York Mayor Rudolph Giuliani
urges President Clinton to free convicted Israeli spy Jonathan
Pollard, a move that could bolster Jewish support for the New York
Republican's prospective Senate campaign. Giuliani says Pollard
deserves clemency because the life sentence for espionage given him
in 1987 goes ``way beyond'' sentences given in the past to
Americans convicted of spying for a U.S. ally. By STEWART M.
POWELL. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   BRADLEY-2000 (Los Angeles) _ Democratic presidential hopeful
Bill Bradley proposes a $65-billion plan to provide universal
access to health insurance, including coverage for all children,
and subsidies for families that cannot afford it. By CRAGG HINES.
