<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; H&AMP;Q &LR;  _ Chase Manhattan Corp., the nation's third-biggest bank, is
buying San Francisco's Hambrecht &AMP; Quist for $1.35 billion, giving
Chase the investment banking business it has coveted for years.
Chase has long expressed a desire to become a bigger player in the
securities business ranging from underwriting stock for new
companies to advising older ones on mergers and acquisitions. By
Sam Zuckerman
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; MUSIC &LR;  _ As a 21-year-old college student, Don MacKinnon was the
guy down the hall who sought out obscure recordings and spent his
free time mixing tapes for friends. As a 31-year-old entrepreneur,
MacKinnon has become the grown-up equivalent of that dormitory
mix-master. While music megastores and mall retailers push
predictable Top 40 releases, MacKinnon's five Hear Music shops
promote a tasteful selection of limited-edition jazz albums,
underground rock 'n' roll, folk songs from Madagascar and 11th
century chant. By Carol Emert
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; GROW &LR;  _ The pluses of an independent contractor. Grow a Business
column by Peter Sinton
</P>
