 &UR; DHL  &LR; _ Are there too many companies jostling for attention on the
small screen? DHL Worldwide Express, the Redwood City package
courier, thinks so and is responding by shifting its ads from the
airwaves to the highways. By David Lazarus
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; FOUNDRY &LR; _ A little-known Sunnyvale company whose equipment lets
Internet service providers offer fast Net access soared 525 percent
in its first day of trading, eclipsing other Net companies that
have gone public this year with record-breaking success. Foundry
Networks, which was priced at just $25, rose $131.25 to close at
$156.25 yesterday. The stock performance gives Foundry, a
networking firm with just 208 employees, a market value of $8.69
billion. By Deborah Solomon
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; GUIDANT &LR;  _ The Food and Drug Administration yesterday approved two
different patches, developed by Bay Area scientists, that are
designed to repair the inner walls of weak blood vessels,
preventing them from bursting and causing death. By Tom Abate
</P>
