<HEADLINE>
L.A. ON BAD RUN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 c.1999 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. _ There is more than the Western Conference
title at stake when the Los Angeles Galaxy plays host to Colorado
tonight at the Rose Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   The Galaxy has tested its playoff mettle the past two games and
failed miserably. But every time Los Angeles has lost under Sigi
Schmid, the former UCLA coach has found a way to bring the team
back and stay away from a big slump.
</P>
<P>
   That's how Schmid has prepared for the MLS playoffs, which begin
in two weeks. He feels you can have one bad game, but you can't
have two consecutive, and certainly not three.
</P>
<P>
   ``Like I've said, it's been a long time since we lost two in a
row,'' Schid said. ``You look at any team in this league and they
go through a series of games where they're going to lose some. And
if you look at our team, we haven't had this type of stretch.''
</P>
<P>
   At least not for a while. The last time the Galaxy lost three in
a row, it fired its coach.
</P>
<P>
   Before back-to-back losses to Colorado and D.C. United, the
Galaxy hadn't dropped two consecutive since May. However, the most
recent defeats seem more troublesome because of the playoff
situation. Instead of leading the Western Conference by four or
eight points, the Galaxy leads the Rapids by a point _ and it's
only three and four points ahead of Dallas and Chicago,
respectively, with three games to play.
</P>
<P>
   Schmid, who hasn't been on the sidelines for the Galaxy's
playoff disasters, was asked why the team seems to sputter in games
that matter most.
</P>
<P>
   ``Every time you read a Galaxy article with us going into the
playoffs, all people can think about is 1996,'' said Schmid,
referring to Los Angeles' 3-2 overtime loss to United in the
inaugural MLS championship. The Galaxy squandered a 2-0 second half
lead.
</P>
<P>
   ``Nineteen-ninety-six was three years ago. Most of the players
that were there are not here now.
</P>
<P>
   ``Have we choked (this year)? No, because we're not in the
playoffs yet. If we play games like this in the playoffs, then
maybe we have choked a little bit.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-28-99 2358EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19990928.0416 </DOCNO>
